%% Diagram: Multi-device cart sync using idempotent line operations
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant Phone
    participant Laptop
    participant CartSvc as Cart Service
    participant Redis
    participant DB as Cart DB
    participant WS as WebSocket Bus

    Phone->>CartSvc: POST /cart/items {sku:A, qty:1, idem:p1}
    CartSvc->>Redis: HSET cart:{u} item:A qty=1
    CartSvc->>DB: upsert (cart_id, sku=A, qty=1) by (cart_id, sku)
    CartSvc-->>Phone: 201 line v=3
    CartSvc->>WS: publish line_changed sku=A qty=1 v=3
    WS-->>Laptop: line_changed sku=A qty=1 v=3
    Note over Laptop: Reconcile local state v=3

    Laptop->>CartSvc: PATCH /cart/items/A {qty:2, idem:l1, ifMatch:v=3}
    CartSvc->>Redis: HSET cart:{u} item:A qty=2 v=4
    CartSvc->>DB: update qty=2 where v=3 returning v=4
    CartSvc-->>Laptop: 200 line v=4
    CartSvc->>WS: publish line_changed sku=A qty=2 v=4
    WS-->>Phone: line_changed sku=A qty=2 v=4

    par Phone retries timed-out POST
        Phone->>CartSvc: POST /cart/items {sku:A, qty:1, idem:p1}
        CartSvc->>Redis: GET idempotency:p1 -> cached 201
        CartSvc-->>Phone: 201 (cached, no-op on cart)
    and Laptop adds different SKU
        Laptop->>CartSvc: POST /cart/items {sku:B, qty:1, idem:l2}
        CartSvc->>DB: upsert sku=B qty=1
        CartSvc-->>Laptop: 201 line v=5
        CartSvc->>WS: publish line_changed sku=B qty=1 v=5
        WS-->>Phone: line_changed sku=B qty=1 v=5
    end
